Project HOPE is an international health care organization founded in the United States in 1958. Project HOPE (Health Opportunities for People Everywhere) is dedicated to providing lasting solutions to health problems with the mission of helping people to help themselves. Identifiable to many by the SS HOPE, the world’s first peacetime hospital ship, Project HOPE provides medical training and health education, as well as conducts humanitarian assistance programs in more than 35 countries.

Over the past five decades, Project HOPE has demonstrated its ability to develop and permanently institute long-term solutions to pressing health problems, the true essence of helping people help themselves.

name: BLACK SEA shirt
description:
The Black Sea was a busy waterway on the crossroads of the ancient world: the Balkans to the West, the Eurasian steppes to the north, Caucasus and Central Asia to the East, Asia Minor and Mesopotamia to the south, and Greece to the south-west. The oldest processed gold in the world, arguably left by Old Europeans, was found in Varna, and the Black Sea was supposedly sailed by the Argonauts. The land at the eastern end of the Black Sea, Colchis, (now Georgia), marked for the Greeks an edge of the known world.

100% cotton, slim fit premium tee.

Cogito ergo sum, "I think, therefore I am", is a philosophical Latin statement proposed by Descartes. The basic meaning of the phrase is that someone wondering whether or not he or she exists is, in and of itself, proof that something, an "I", exists to do the thinking.

name: URSUS ARCTOS HORRIBILIS shirt
description:
The grizzly bear (Ursus arctos horribilis), also known as the silvertip bear, is a subspecies of brown bear (Ursus arctos) that generally lives in the uplands of western North America. This subspecies is thought to descend from Ussuri brown bears which crossed to Alaska from Eastern Russia 100,000 years ago, though they did not move south until 13,000 years ago. They are an endangered species.

100% cotton, slim fit premium tee.

name: DEATH'S HEAD MOTH tee shirt
description:
The Death's-head Hawkmoth or Death's Head Sphinx refers to any one of the 3 species (A. atropos, A. styx and A. lachesis) of moth in the genus Acherontia.

The species name Atropos is related to death, derived from atropos that may not be turned. Atropos was one of the three Moirai, goddesses of fate and destiny. In addition the genus name Acherontia is derived from Acheron, a river in Greece, which in Greek mythology was known as the river of pain, and was one of the five rivers of the Greek underworld.

Edgar Allan Poe's short story The Sphinx describes a close encounter with a death's-headed sphinx moth, describing it as “the genus Sphinx, of the family Crepuscularia of the order Lepidoptera.”

This tee is extremely limited edition, only 50 prints in total.

Chaos ----- Sudden change ----- Impact ----- Hard times
Crisis ----- Revelation ----- Disruption ----- Realizing the truth
Disillusion ----- Crash ----- Burst ----- Uncomfortable experience
Downfall ----- Ruin ----- Ego blow ----- Explosive transformation
